Defines the compiled configuration for a single `bwrap` sandbox launch, plus the fixed cage-internal path constants that both this crate and other files depend on for their exact string values.

The path constants (`CAGE_BIN`, `CAGE_RULES_PATH`, `CAGE_RUN_DIR`, `API_SOCK_NAME`, `CAGE_CLAUDE_CONFIG`, `CAGE_CLAUDE_CRED`, `CAGE_LOCAL_CLAUDE`) are the cage-side mount targets; anything elsewhere in the crate that builds bwrap args or synthesizes `~/.claude.json`/credentials must bind to these exact strings or the sandboxed process won't find its files. `CAGE_RUN_DIR`/`API_SOCK_NAME` together form the API proxy socket path (`{CAGE_RUN_DIR}/{API_SOCK_NAME}`) — change one without the other and the proxy becomes unreachable. `CAGE_CLAUDE_CRED` and `CAGE_LOCAL_CLAUDE` are rooted at `/tmp` specifically because the cage's `HOME` is set to `/tmp`, not because of any general convention.

`BwrapConfig` is a plain data struct (`Debug, Clone, Default`), assembled elsewhere and consumed by the bwrap arg-builder. Notable fields: `mask_file` must point to a real empty regular file, never `/dev/null` — bind mounts are `nodev`, so masking a secret with a device node makes every open on it fail with EACCES (this broke git reading a masked `.git/config`). `target_root` is bound at the *same* absolute path inside and outside the cage, unlike other binds which get cage-local aliases — required so build artifacts referencing absolute paths remain valid in both contexts. `new_session` defaults semantics are inverted by use case: `true` (safe default) blocks TIOCSTI injection for non-interactive runs, `false` is needed for interactive TUI rendering. `env` is exhaustive: paired with `--clearenv` in the bwrap invocation, so any variable not listed here is simply absent in the cage.